            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p></p> <!--  -->
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Assumed connection with the Italika Rhomaia Sebasta Isolumpia, the quinquennial or quadrennial sacred games, were established in Naples in 2 BCE and first celebrated in 2 CE, were originally devoted to the worship of Augustus whilst he was alive. The games were celebrated at least until the third or fourth centuries CE.</p> 
